  "description": [
    "art ducaliort by Wit H LEVITT International Education Director SERVICEMEN IN THE POSTWAR Recent letters from men in the armed forces to our office have complained bitterly about the amount of confusion and lack of specific planning to take care of returning soldiers during the post war period Several of the men who have written us tell about how they have been told about how the unions are going to keep us from getting our jobs back and how they will face the same problems the returning soldiers of World War I faced Such thoughts in the minds of the men in the armed forces can hardly be con sidered as morale building Of ebust any union man in the armed forces probably knows dif ferently and any who have been able to get the unions Postwar Program knows what the unions are fighting for OUR POSTWAR PLAN In the Postwar Plan adopted by our International Executive Board our union Tnakes the fol lowing statement Our soldiers and sailors are today concerned with the Nations first jobto win the war It is our responsibility to make certai that their services will be honored by something more practical than a silver"
